def: Unprejudiced; just; judicial; honest.-- Fair"*mind`ed*ness, n.
The common burdock; the clotbur. [Obs.] Wyclif.
Not sociable; not inclined to society; averse to companionshipor conversation; solitary; reserved; as, an unsociable person ortemper.-- Un*so"cia*ble*ness, n.-- Un*so"cia*bly, adv.
Dissolution of the marriage tie; divorce; separation.Let him write her a divorcement. Deut. xxiv. 1.The divorcement of our written from our spoken language. R. Morris.
A state of being complicate or intricate. Mitford.
One of a religious order of regular canons founded by St.Norbert at Prémontré, in France, in 1119. The members of the orderare called also White Canons, Norbertines, and Premonstrants.
A glucoside found in the bearberry (and others of theEricaceæ), and extracted as a bitter, yellow, amorphous mass.
